The body of an unidentified woman was found along the N2 near Young Park at about 2am on Sunday. Police spokesman Warrant Officer Alwin Labans said the woman, whose body was bruised, was partly clothed. “The woman’s jersey and bag were found nearby,” he said. There was no form of identification among the woman’s things. Six hours later, an unidentified body was found floating in a river near the quarry in Hawarthia Drive, Malabar. “The man was partly clothed, gagged, and his hands were tied behind his back,” Labans said. A 17-year-old boy who was stabbed was among the victims of three murders reported to police in Port Elizabeth at the weekend. Police spokesman Warrant Officer Alwin Labans said the police had been called to a house in Malabar Extension on Friday night, where Eashra Kiwiet’s body had been discovered.… December 12, 2016 The body of a 23-year-old woman was found in a house in Polar Park Street in Mandela Village yesterday morning. Police confirmed Marilyn Smith was found inside the house and was believed to have been strangled. Police spokesman Warrant Officer Alwin Labans said details remained sketchy as detectives were still… January 9, 2017 A pedestrian made the gruesome discovery of a murder victim who had been axed to death, and had the axe still lodged in her head, in Missionvale early yesterday. The body of Nobengazi Notshoba, 49, was found in an open field near Tromp Street at about 6.30am. Police spokesman Warrant Officer… April 20, 2017